  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Google does not share exact details about the size of its database publicly. Google's infrastructure encompasses an enormous amount of data spread across numerous data centers globally. It includes data from its search index, user accounts, various cloud services, and numerous other products such as YouTube, Gmail, Google Maps, Google Photos, and more.\n\nEstimates suggest that Google's data capacity is in the exabytes range, where 1 exabyte is equal to 1 billion gigabytes. However, the precise size is difficult to pin down and continually growing given the rapid accumulation and processing of data.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, you'd need to refer to official Google disclosures or detailed reports from industry analysts.",
